			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Debug book: add Lae'Zel to your party&#xD;&#xA;Debug book: go to the Plains, near the gith chokepoint&#xD;&#xA;teleport -130, 542&#xD;&#xA;Skip through that dialogue&#xD;&#xA;Approach the gith&#xD;&#xA;Take a branch through the gith chokepoint dialogue that will end in hostility, so fail a check or attack them.&#xD;&#xA;ReCon: killcombat&#xD;&#xA;Lae'Zel should speak to you, triggering GLO_GithChokepoint_WRD_Laezel." />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="118" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="You speak to Lae'zel after the choke point confrontation with a githyanki knight. She is absolutely infuriated - and, though she doesn't outwardly show it, frightened. She may have been targeted by her own queen.&#xA;" />
